description:
Dance of Destruction

Chapter 14 of Avaiyo, Vol. 03

Heading back to Brosha, Sekken and Iyo meet up with their guild, Emerald Moon. Reunions are cut short as a new crisis emerges that has the means to threaten the entire world. With little time to spare, they depart for Preminx...in hopes of heading off the Dark Legion. With Emerald Moon standing between two armies, it is their hope the Region of Preminx will not be soaked in blood.
name: Dance of Destruction

description:
Feast Before Peace

Black Ham and Hot Dog must deliver vital intelligence to Col. Bird in order to begin the rebellion against the Salad Colonial Government, but General Gourd, ORGANIC, and the Church of MochaTaco have other plans.
name: Feast Before Peace

description:
Life After Death

She's alive! She's Alive! She's AAALLLIIIIIVE! Follow the rebirth of Detective Tuesday in this blast from the past story during a dream of her days with Frankie!
name: Life After Death

description:
The second issue of an ongoing mini-comics series, a one-man anthology of odd comics by Jamie Tanner.

This issue's contents: "The Wanderings of the Young Girl Giant", "AMUSEMENT", and more selections from "Always On Brand", a series of experiments in nonsensical marketing-speak poetry.
Join us for another fantastic issue featuring Mort Meskin Magic! Collecting Young Romance and Young Love stories from the summer of 1950, plus a free bonus surprise tale!

The Cruel Dance Music of the Universe -Part 3

Bob explains to his friend (Bon Zoffo) how he was kidnapped by purple 3-eyed apes and taken to a secret underground super-computer that conjured them into existence. -Also features cute & fuzzy hell-hounds, bad stock market suggestions and your friendly next door neighbor... Mr. Kthulhu.
name: The Cruel Dance Music of the Universe - Part 3

story_arc_credits.name: The Cruel Dance Music of the Universe

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Cruel Dance Music of the Universe

description:
Fad Deity

Lou is surprised to find that a man he accidentally stranded on a barren planet, now worships him as a god.
name: Fad Deity

description:
The noise of thunder, part ten.

MANIFEST continues its extravagant ride in the tradition of 70's/80's adult comix!

An unexpected event leads Tessa Theus into an even less predictable situation. Like the Wayfarer once said to her: "Nothing can be completely destroyed," especially the past.

An issue that will make you scream "Safe space!" even after its end!
name: The Noise of Thunder, Part Ten

description:
Things turn from bad to worse for our true blue hero (and convicted felon) Ned Kelly.

Not only has the colony of Victoria been invaded by hostile aliens who masquerade as Policemen, but Ned's philandering past has also come back to bite him!

A chance encounter with old flame Alice Sherritt at the resistance base leads to fisticuffs, betrayal, and more!
name: Episode Two

description:
And beyond the others?

Prince Charming meets two mutant sisters: Gala and Shea. He falls in love with a beautiful mutant princess and finds out what a poetic license is. He learns a little history and gets a life lesson.

The awkward feelings between Louise and Bruce are growing, though it seems like Louise will never realize what's going on in Bruce's head. But when Bruce's family runs into even more financial trouble and he needs money fast, a modeling competition may be the best-and most embarrassing-way to solve all his problems at once.
name: Volume 2

description: Out of the Blue: A Collection of Campfire Tales conjures 175 pages of surprising, strange, and spooky stories evoking the best tradition of campfire tales. Contributors include award nominated comic creators as well as talented newcomers.
name: A Collection of Campfire Tales

description: Betty and Veronica are ready for some secret agent action! Join them as they use high-tech gadgets and karate kicks to save the day from the forces of evil! Can they rescue the kidnapped Archie from a mysterious foe?
name: Agents Betty & Veronica

description:
Black Rose

This is the 5th issue in the Prisoner of the Mind series. Cole soon fears that staying alive will test his moral fiber and his friendships. He doesn't know who to trust and he even questions himself. Cole tries everything to get to the bottom of it, but the only person holding the key is abducted right before his eyes. Will he reunite with Jasmine, his former lover and clear his name, or remain a wanted man?
name: Black Rose

description: Stranded on a strange world, Shump is in a whole mess of trouble. Will local sheriff Rose Calamity be able to keep him safe?

2015 may be over, but the fun has just begun! Join us as we look back at all the hilarious new stories that debuted in our Comics Double Digest series in 2015. Laugh along with Archie, Jughead, Betty and the whole gang in these stories, drawn in the traditional Archie style!
Troubled gunfighter John Comb haunts the Old West with a terrible secret: bitten by the werewolf who murdered his lover, Comb must hunt the wolf's Sire to break it's horrible curse.
Set during the last days of WWII, a conscientious objector named Hegland finds himself hunted by a phantom in the woods of Northern Germany.

volume.name: Cazadores EsotÃ©ricos: El Regreso de los Templarios

description: Twenty years ago, Nuclear and biological warfare ravaged the planet. Now, a sheltered group of humans are forced into the outside world to face the reality of their new lives and the mutated humans who now roam the surface.

Highway #1 in Afghanistan from Kabul to Kandahar is the world's most dangerous highway.

It is often referred to as the "highway to hell" or "hell's highway".

A United States military convoy is assigned with transporting a BBC news crew from Kandahar to Naw Abad, the BBC news crew wants to report on the war in Afghanistan and they quickly realize that the real story of the war is the Highway itself.

Between Taliban attacks, Car bombs, treacherous narrow corners and roadways, the BBC news crew find out first hand why it's called the world's most dangerous highway.

Our lives are shaped by the choices we make. Is it ever possible to truly know the extent of those choices, how much each one changes our life? Meet Jake, a soldier in Afghanistan fighting the war on terror. In an instant he is thrown into something he cannot explain, much less accept that it is real. Jake has a choice to make, a choice that will ultimately determine his fate. In this exciting new miniseries, from Manik Creations, Death's Life, is a story about the journey of life and more importantly where that life takes you.

The second volume of the "Cyclecircus" collection familiarises us with the plight of the Bushmen people in the country of Botswana. The Kalahari Bushmen are the oldest people in Africa. For a long time they have been oppressed to such an extent that their existence as a group is under threat. The discovery of diamonds on their land accelerated the destruction of this ancestral culture. The desert sands of the Kalahari are home to Roy Sesana, Bushmen leader, winner of the "Right Livelihood Award", known as the "Alternative Nobel Prize". Roy Sesana will tell us his story, which is also that of his people. A tragic story, but when all is said ando done, one which is still very much alive and which has not yet reached its end.

The powerful corporate entity known as Bren Werks has been secretly experimenting on human test subjects for their own nefarious use. One test subject, Experiment X-51 has recently escaped with the aid of a young man by the name of Jimmy. Together they will try to rescue other experiments and expose the truth behind the alien race that runs Bren Werks. Watch the action unfold as Bren Werks throws everything they have at these Lost Warriors trying to take them down.

Jack of Spades, Vol. 1: A Wild Card collects The Origin of Plasmaster (from Source Point Presents #1), Jack of Spades #0, Jack of Spades: Lonely Tower Lives (from Alter Egos Volume 1), Jack of Spades #1, and exclusive bonus content.

As the growing threat of the parahuman population rages, the Nuevas Vegas police force begin taking new precautions. But only one man is successful in bringing down this new wave of super-powered crime, the masked P.I. known only as The Jack of Spades. In a city ruled by criminal organizations, can Spade truly get the job done? And where does he fit in with the mounting politics? Packed with action and a pulp noir appeal, this collection is the perfect intro to Trico Lutkins' unique world of characters and its #1 wild card, the Jack of Spades.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Jack of Spades: A Wild Card

description: 100 years ago, one of the great tragedies of the twentieth century began on June 28, 1914. The assassination of the heir to the throne Franz Ferdinand and his wife in Sarajevo set in motion a chain reaction that ended in what is today known as WWI. At the time Austrian writer Karl Kraus wrote his epic masterpiece "The last Days of Mankind", about the sentiments during the time of the war which seems as relevant today as it was back then. Reporting mostly from the point of view of Austrian society in Vienna, this satirical and eye-opening graphic novel teaches us one thing; In regards to war, mankind has learned absolutely nothing in 100 years.
A skeleton attempts to live among human beings
Collection of Issues 5-8
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: The Misadventures of Electrolyte and The Justice Purveyors: ThinkTank's Gambit

description: The pen, ink, and wash images of this graphic novel speak louder than words in relating a soldier's experiences during World War I, from his initial enthusiasm to his ultimate disillusionment. A dramatic narrative by Hungarian veteran Szegedi SzÃ¼ts portrays the tragedy of wartime life on the battlefield as well as on the home front. Includes new Foreword by Peter Kuper. Contains adult material.
name: GN

description: Trade Paperback collecting Naked Man Comics #1-8 plus bonus material.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Naked Man Comics: Naked and The City

description: Taking place in the mid 1800s, Roy Whales is a cowboy out hunting buffalo. While hunting, he catches a fever and at the same time a sickness spreads in his home town of Red Town. Village folk are acting erratic and are quarantined. Roy, who is thought to be infected, is thrown in with the sick and sent off into th...e ocean on a boat to die. The adventure really begins when Roy finds the ship has wrecked on an island with pirates!

Masquerade

A series of brutal murders are occurring in Nam City. All the victims belong to different criminal organizations; the police suspect a gang war but they are searching for a sole individual, a man with a helmet and a leather jacket with a tiger on the back.
name: Masquerade

description:
Tighe, the confused boy, struggles to find himself. Tracey, the girl with too much ambition, struggles to make it big. Alison, the girl with no ambition, struggles to ignore her meddling friends. And Mike struggles to find someone to love.

Sharing a hip Saint Louis apartment, these friends face only the problems we all deal with... finding jobs, boyfriends, bars, and bands. Their struggles end only as they begin to grow up.

Originally presented as "Meet Me in Saint Louie" on the Modern Tales Longplay site in June 2003, this edition adds more than 20 pages of new story and art, and many extras.

Enter a world of pure terror in one of the most anticipated Graphic Novels of the year!! When a foolish antique collector reads the inscription on the back of an ancient Chinese amulet, she unleashes the ultimate evil. The Unwanted follows the heart-pounding saga of a group of streetwise teens trapped inside an inescapable juvenile detention facility, facing a relentless evil that will stop at nothing to consume them. And their souls... Beautifully illustrated by artist Juan Romera, The Unwanted is already being hailed by reviewers as the next horror classic.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: The Further Adventures of Nyoka the Jungle Girl
General Mills Presents: Batman and the Scarecrow

description: The title of this issue is not Flax; the publisher put the Swedish/Norwegian version of this title on the cover.

Ashes of the Immortals

Travel to the far reaches of the galaxy to a distant world around a dim sun where science has managed to conquer death itself. Meet Rookie Investigator Nos as he is handed his first case since becoming a Constable for his District: The first murder anywhere on the planet since the scientists of his world discovered the secret to immortality. The murder leads Nos to a conspiracy that extends across his dark world and may reduce his society it to ashes. It's first death in a over a thousand years, but will it be the last?
name: Ashes of the Immortals

description: Celebrate the 75th anniversary of Archie Comics with this special retrospective presentation! Making her debut WAY back in 1943, Ginger got her own 10-issue series in 1952 after making several guest-star appearances in Zip and Suzie Comics. A fascinating snapshot of the 1950s, Ginger's wacky antics involve her on-and-off boyfriend Ickky, her grumpy dad, and more! Join us as we present some of the funniest stories from the series, from crazy clothing to school dance disasters!
name: Ginger, Sweetheart of A Nation

description:
A World Threatened...

Once again, the Tamiran Empire is trying to establish itself as the supreme world power. Now known as the Dark Legion, they're raising underground armies throughout the world to overthrow the civilizations of Xiltria.

Within the Region of Preminx, the discovery of their encampment has forced their hand. Marching from one city to another, nothing is safe as they kill anyone who knows of their existence.

The first city to fall is Lokili. Ruins are left in the Dark Legion's wake as they abandon the decimated city and head for Orabal. However, it's impossible to keep such carnage a secret. Without a moments breath, news begins to circulate around the Nation. Mercenaries and guilds alike join forces to thwart the Dark Legion's march. With their whereabouts now disclosed to the entire world, they have two choices: continue on towards Orabal, or return to protect their hideout.

Amidst the chaos, Emerald Moon has discovered their hidden base and plan to overthrow it before the army returns.

While successfully infiltrating the encampment, Emerald Moon now stands before the very heart of the Dark Legion. In their efforts to destroy the Command Center, they've unwillingly become pinned between an impenetrable barrier and an army of undead Neyens. With danger coming from all sides, Fayli, Lage and Eyader have only one choice...to engage the enemy.

Avaiyo: Myriad Law

Preminx Part I

Chapters 043 - 056
name: Volume 04

description:
From the creators of Afterlife Inc. and 7STRING comes Big Punch Magazine, a quarterly magazine serialising four ongoing series from the Big Punch Multiverse.

Can it be, dear reader? Is this really the end of the first, thrilling year of BPM? As the days grow colder at Big Punch Towers, we're wrapping up warm and cracking open the mulled wine to welcome in our first ever winter issue! The year might be ending, but the adventure is only just beginning for BPM! Read on, dear reader, for tales of endings, beginnings, and strange awakenings...

Even though Oto has a fever, she's been brought to an exclusive hotel opening by one very pushy Airi. Feeling like a fish out of water among all the wealthy guests, Oto escapes the party to go soak in one of the numerous hot springs at the hotel. Haruto has the same idea. But when the sign outside his bath gets switched, he gets a little more than he bargained for!
name: Chapter 21

description: John Corvus, agent of DIS, continues his investigation into the ritual beheading of a British government minister. Following a hallucinogenic trail across London, Corvus searches for the source of the secret radio transmissions broadcast by the satanic cult Tempel Satanas.
name: The Satan Machine

description:
The Flight of Fortune's Favor

The epic adventure returns with an issue three years in the making! Dracula and Thalia have escaped London aboard an airship bound for Europe, but Varney, the new Lord of the Vampires, isn't going to let them go without a fight. Come aboard for air pirates, lightning engines and the fistfight of the century in... The Flight of Fortune's Favor!
name: The Flight of Fortune's Favor

description:
Space Oddity part one of two

Deep in the woods of , Oregon a trio of aliens fight to stay alive and one step ahead of Agents Hill and Phelps. What secrets do these strange visitors from another world hold? One way or another, the Agents are determined to find out...
name: Space Oddity Part One of Two

description:
What Makes A Hero? Part 1

Someone new has come to Delta City! But who is the mysterious "Captain Delta"? Find out in "What Makes A Hero? Part 1"!
name: What Makes A Hero? Part 1

description:
2015 Sticky Edition

The 2015 Sticky Edition of Job Dun, Fat Assassin is here!

4 new stories! 6 new characters! Same number of fat-ass killer!

Oh, and a porn-store. There's a porn-store.

Join Job Dun as he liberates a hole-hungry data leak from the clutches of a slap-happy Dictator, battles thrill-gun Bombshells and revenge-filled Genre-Bots - and takes a girl out on a date!

Written by Mark Hobby, this 24 page, full-colour comic has art by Tom Bonin (with Lancelot Catan on colours), Dave Bus, Kev Harper and Joe Palmer. With letters by Bolt-01!

Buy this suka!

John L. Sullivan's is banged up from the 1st fight. Dawk uses his healing tanks and scientific methods to get JLS back to fighting shape ASAP. It's a needed because his next fight is in 7 days. Buque spends some time looking over John's next opponent. It's a big bruiser that can cause far more damage than the last. Buque looks for a weakness and then hope that JLS listens to his strategy. John L. exits the healing tank unscarred and amazed at how fast he is back in shape. He isn't aware that the next time the healing process is used it may not work as smoothly.

volume.name: John L. Sullivan Boston Strong Boy In Space

description:
Welcome to Barbados 2015, one of the world's prime tourist destinations, home to some of the best golf courses, casinos, luxurious night life and outrageous parties. Beautiful beach front properties and manmade islands add glitz and glamour ......but Barbados has a dark side.

The story continues after an incident in the Black Bush housing area, leaves some dealers nursing gunshot wounds, others fatally wounded and the residents of the area left calling for help. As time progressed our characters settle back in to their normal lives. But then entered a new player to the game, Dwayne.

From the Shuster award winning creators of Least I Could Do and Gutters comes a loving nod to classic fantasy novels that manages to flip the genre on it's head. Unlikely heros cut a swath through a fantasy world that is extremely familiar and yet very different. A naive elven hunter makes an strange friend in an undead warlock and the two manage to make both enemies and friends as they fight the good fight against the Legaran Empire.

Loose Cannons

Lou finally tracks down Bart Ender. But Captain Tarpa has finally tracked down Lou....
name: Loose Cannons

description: Whether you have bullies for schoolmates, a child predator after you in a locked museum, or just a very nasty parent, it's good to have a mummy looking out for you.
name: Mummy's Boy

description:
Split

"A universe in peril over centuries long plague is now under direct threat for a planar assault. With Mages of all races losing life and sanity to the "Taint" there is no one to turn to for the closure of mysterious gates letting in perils from a world of shadows. What is causing this galaxy wide assault? Is the Taint itself involved?"

Searching for a way out of the wastes the team managed to come upon an open gate to some other place- and standing before it a great dragon. Left with few choices they gang splits, divided by prejudice and duty. The PALADIN's accompany the only remaining Magister back into town, looking for his comm crystal, while Kaiya, Mili, and Duncan return to the temple where Kaiya was taken. Their goal? Reclaiming the ships left by the PALADIN's to find and rescue Toran.
name: Split

description:
The clean man

Amatheus reaches a starport, where he meets a techno-mage. He finds out a few things about his past and about the world he lives in. Panza tries his luck with a song. The mage and the prince arrive at the place where The Gate is. The gate takes one beyond, if he is genetically clean.
name: The Clean Man

description: Chet, Lisa, and Scorpion Umbrella head over to Rome, where they learn the secret of the magical pajama pants. But are The Pants all there is to be found?

Subject K: Part 5

The first arc comes to a close as Pale Man lays out his plan for Subject K. The Resistance decodes some game-changing intelligence. Subject K looks for an ally on the station. WX releases some of his rage.
name: Subject K: Part 5

description: It's time to hit the football field once again with Archie and friends! We've collected some of our favorite football stories for you in this issue of Pep Digital. Can Archie score the winning touchdown? Will Reggie be a team player? Will Moose crush the entire rival team single-handedly? Find out inside!
name: Archie's Touchdown Tales

description: Mirai Kakehashi may have received the powers of an angel, but his life is far from bliss. With 11 others like him all battling for the position of the next god, things are getting dangerous. One candidate has started dressing like a superhero and eliminating the competition. And on Mirai's first day of high school, he's shot with the red arrow of love by the girl he's always had a crush on!
name: Chapter 4: Heart's Beloved

description:
Based on Rikki-Tikki-Tavi from Rudyard Kipling's The Jungle Book.

With Nagaina and her brood about to attack his new family, Rikki pleads with the Chakram clan to join his battle to save the humans.
Truths are revealed. Heroes and villains show their true stripes. Magical tattoo fairies do their stuff. And life and death, as always, are in the palm of Shaman's hand.

The Chippewa Vendetta - Part 2

Silvertongue, our favorite space-time district attorney, finds that his case got a bit tougher than he thought --encountering what he least expected: aliens from the future, (or "ghosts", as they call them). Will he and his team arrive to a guilty verdict? Will he survive the hazardous, unexpected, intellectual alien attack? There's only one way to find out, in this epic conclusion to The Chippewa Vendetta.
name: The Chippewa Vendetta - Part 2

description:
If you thought Obamacare was confusing, wait until you see the Smurfs tackle the medical profession!

When one Smurf steps up as doctor he starts a fever-for more doctors! Soon, a hospital is built in the Smurf Village and it rapidly fills up with all sorts of wacky cases. But how much help are these new doctors actually giving their patients?

As usual, only Papa Smurf can provide the remedy for the latest Smurfs craze.

It's another classic Smurfs adventure from master cartoonist Peyo.

Note: The digital edition (2/3/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Doctor Smurf

description:
The Thea Sisters are five fun, lively students at Mouseford Academy on Whale Island, who want to be real, live journalists, just like their hero, Thea Stilton. Between classes, friendships, crushes, and some bizarre mysteries to solve, they find life to be a never-ending adventure!

Note: The digital edition (2/3/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: The Secret of the Waterfall in the Woods

description:
Run, Chloie, Run!

Zoe's gonna knock Knave off her revenge list... but not if TransCat has anything to say about it! More action and less romance! Come at me, bro!
name: Run, Chloie, Run!

description: As Henry recovers, he finds a kindred spirit in Kallose's impressionable sister, Lina. Meanwhile, Kallose and Garth begin to unravel the mystery of the "doppelgÃ¤nger syndrome" that threatens to kill all the subjects.
name: Vol. 2
